Minimum versions are those which were used for testing - thus, perhaps
older versions work as well ...

compile time:
- C++ compiler (GCC g++ for example)
- C compiler (GCC for example)
- GNU make >= 3.81
- C++ Standard Library
- boost >=  1.36
  - Accumulators
  - Format
  - Integer
  - Lexical Cast
  - Pool
  - Smart Ptr

  - Date Time
  - Program Options
- lapack >= 3.2.1
- ksh93 - or - bash >= 2.03.0(1) (only needed for test scripts)


runtime:
- boost >=  1.36
  - Date Time
  - Program Options
- lapack >= 3.2.1